Student’s protests are flaring in Kwazulu-Natal. Mangosuthu University of Technology students have blockaded roads in and out of Umlazi. On Wednesday they blockaded the institution's main entrance with burning tyres and debris. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 UMLAZI - Protesting students clashed with police at the Mangosuthu University of Technology in Umlazi on Thursday. Students used burning tyres and debris to block the institution's main entrance. It is understood their protest is part of the national shutdown of higher learning institutions campaign. READ: Social media post leads to DUT chaos The students are protesting against financial exclusion and the scrapping of historical debt among other issues. This article has been updated. More details to follow when available eNCA's @DasenThathiah is outside the main gate at the Mangosuthu University of Technology. Students have blockaded the institution's main entrance. #MUTstudentprotest #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/ahYEBjmAQy MUT students have blockaded roads in and out of Umlazi. It is understood it is part of the national shutdown of high learning campaign calling for the scrapping of historical debt and financial exclusion among other concerns. @DasenThathiah has more details. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/0oS5KGp5fD